transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, ma'am. I had purchased some...

Speaker 1: Viagra?

Speaker 2: Yeah, online.

Speaker 1: Uh-huh.

Speaker 2: And didn't realize it was a subscription.

Speaker 1: I want to cancel the subscription.

Speaker 2: No problem, Clifford. I can help you out.

Speaker 1: Can you just confirm your date of birth?

Speaker 2: 18-19-53.

Speaker 1: Thank you so much. I see you're a VIP status customer.

Speaker 2: Oh, I see the doctor put you on monthly refills, which you're not required to have.

Speaker 1: How's the medication working out for you?

Speaker 2: It's not.

Speaker 1: Okay, that's what I was asking. Do you happen to have the pills on you by chance?

Speaker 2: No, I don't.

Speaker 1: Okay, because here I see the pharmacy notes.

Speaker 2: It looks like they just sent you the regular generic Viagra.

Speaker 1: You did not receive the AGV?

Speaker 2: That's correct.

Speaker 1: Yeah, give me a second. I'm going to get you out a replacement.

Speaker 2: The pharmacy must have ran out of the AGV, and they didn't tell us.

Speaker 1: No, that's okay.

Speaker 2: Well, I can get you out the correct medication as a replacement free of charge,

Speaker 1: because you received the incorrect medication in the first place.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay, give me one second.

Speaker 2: Give me a second, and then I'll tell you how you can confirm you received the correct medication.

Speaker 1: I'm just going to switch it to 100 milligrams as well.

Speaker 2: All right, perfect.

Speaker 1: Okay, so when you get this new bottle in the mail in a few days, it's going to say AGV on the bottle,

Speaker 2: but it's also going to say the name Greenstone.

Speaker 1: And Greenstone is the name of Pfizer's pharmacy in France.

Speaker 2: And then on the pill, the only number imprinted is going to be the number 100.

Speaker 1: And those are the two ways you can confirm you received the Pfizer AGV Viagra,

Speaker 2: because right now your bottles probably say APCO, and on the pill it says AC something.

Speaker 1: And then what I'm going to do, I'm going to go ahead and pause your refills for six months.

Speaker 2: I'm going to pause it until July 31st.

Speaker 1: That way, if I cancel it now, it's going to delete your profile,

Speaker 2: and the pharmacy will not be able to send you out the correct replacement.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: I'll give you my extension so you can call me back and let me know how the AGV works out for you.

Speaker 1: Hang on a second.

Speaker 2: No problem.

Speaker 1: Take your time.

Speaker 2: Go ahead.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: It's 0020, and my name is Michelle.

Speaker 1: Michelle, thank you very much.

Speaker 2: No problem, Clifford.

Speaker 1: Have a great day.

Speaker 2: You too.

Speaker 1: Thanks.

Speaker 2: Thanks.

Speaker 1: Bye.

Speaker 2: Bye.
